{
  "name": "cbd",
  "description": "Urban CBD grid with TWIN FEEDERS. SUB-X is outaged with four feeders on three breakers: X1 (solo, double-ring riser) and X2 (solo, retail tee) each on their own CB, while X3 and X4 form a TWIN PAIR sharing CB-X34 through a common riser XR-34 that splits to both feeder heads, so the express feeder and the secondary spur lose supply together. On the healthy side SUB-A's A1 and A2 are a twin pair on CB-A12; SUB-B..F feeders are solo. Six healthy sources, twelve tie paths incl. parallel ties into the same feeder pair (the meshed case a pure edge-count radiality test cannot catch); tight ratings force several sectionalizing splits and partial shed.",
